      • getSPARQLRewriting

        public String getSPARQLRewriting(String sparql)
                          throws OBDAException
        Rewrites the given input SPARQL query and returns back an expanded SPARQL query. The query expansion involves query transformation from SPARQL algebra to Datalog objects and then translating back to SPARQL algebra. The transformation to Datalog is required to apply the rewriting algorithm.
        Specified by:
        getSPARQLRewriting in interface OBDAStatement
        Parameters:
        sparql - The input SPARQL query.
        Returns:
        An expanded SPARQL query.
        Throws:
        OBDAException - if errors occur during the transformation and translation.

      • getUnfolding

        public String getUnfolding(String strquery)
                    throws Exception
        Returns the SQL query for a given SPARQL query. In the process, the signature of the query will be set into the query container and the jena Query object created (or cached) will be set as jenaQueryContainer[0] so that it can be used in other process after getUnfolding. If the query is not already cached, it will be cached in this process.
        Parameters:
        strquery -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        Exception
